review_blob: Not bad for a light beer.  Similar to any American light beer, light malt aroma, clear pour.  Taste is malt, no hops.  Over OK when compared to an American light beer.
Not bad for a light beer.  Similar to any American light beer, light malt aroma, clear pour.  Taste is malt, no hops.  Over OK when compared to an American light beer.

It would be good with food, but taste like a light american lager, nothing special.  Poured very clear golden color with a good size head.  Taste is similar to any american light beer. Fun to drink because of the look of the bottle.

Malt aroma, not much hops.  Poured a dark gold.  Taste is sweet with bittering hops, no aroma hops.  Overall a general pale ale that isnt bad.  I believe the demographic this beer is produced for matches the flavor profile, but people on this website would want the outlaw beer outlawed.
Nice light beer.  Good balance of orange and malts.  Not much hops.  It was very refreshing, I plan on getting this one during the summer.
beer_name: Buffalo Bills Orange Blossom Cream Ale

review_blob: bread, cereal, citrus, floral, dough, earthy, golden, clear, white foam, lightly bitter, light sweetness, medium body, average carbonation,
Amber pour with a small head. Aroma is malty with some citrus hops.  Taste is slight bitter.  Not a bad IPA.
Pours a dark amber with a small head.  Light malt aroma slight bitter taste.  Overall an OK beer.
Really good IPA, sweet with a good amount of hops.  One of my favorites.  Aroma is sweet with a good hop nose.  Copper color pour with a good head.  Taste is sweet then a nice bitter.
beer_name: Deschutes Red Chair Northwest Pale Ale

review_blob: Orange pour with a normal sized head.  Aroma of hops, floral and grass.  Taste is similar to the aroma with some malt.  Overall not bad.
caramel, roasty, floral, grass, amber, clear, white foam, medium sweetness, very bitter, full body, average carbonation,
Aroma is sweet malt and some hops.  Poured a dark amber and a normal head. Taste is sweet then bitter.  Wanted more citric hops.  Overall an OK IPA.

Beer pours a cloudy pale yellow with a good head.  I dont like it, it taste like a liquid yeast packet.  I have had a lot better kolsch beers, didnt like this one.  There was large chunks of yeast floating in it.

My first chili beer I ever had I didnt like it.  I got this one in a create a 6 pack.  It really wasnt that bad at all, I had it with some mexican food and it really paired well. Just a slight malt flavor then you really can taste the peppers.  Not overly spicy, but well balanced.  Something I wouldnt drink a lot but it would be something I get again.
Aroma of hops and caramel.  Pours a clear brown with a large head.  Taste is sweet and bitter hops.  Smooth on the palate.  Overall a great beer.
Aroma is dark chocolate and caramel.  It poured a dark brown with a brown head.  Taste is sweet malt with a little bitter.  Full body beer.
This is a good IPA, only this is I wished for more hoppy aroma.  Copper clear pour with a decent head.  Sweet and bitter taste, lightly hopped.  Overall not bad, but my taste likes more hops.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Pours amber with a large head.  Aroma is sweet, not much hops or malt.  Taste is light, good balance of bitter and sweet. Over all it was ok.
Sweet aroma, pours amber, slight hops taste... wanted more hops.  Not horrible, but wanted more hops.
beer_name: Boulder Beer Hazed Hoppy Session Ale

review_blob: Smells like bananas and yeast.  Pours very clear with a large head.  Taste similar to the smell at first, not much after taste.  Im not a fan of Belgian style beers so not my favorite.
Nice hoppy aroma and poured an amber color, medium head.  Taste very hoppy and bitter.  Overall not a bad IPA.
Pours orange-gold colored with a normal head. Aroma is floral and grapefruits.  Taste is lighter bodied with hoppy bitterness. Not a bad IPA.
Great hoppy IPA, strong aroma, poured orange with a normal head.  Taste is sweet, bitter and hoppy.  Overall one of the better IPAs I have had.

Not what I expected but not bad.  Light hops for an IPA.  Aroma is sweet, light brown in color.  Taste is more malt than hop... wonder if the bottle was miss labeled.  Overall not bad, but not like a normal IPA.
Earthy hop aroma and poured a dark orange with a small white head.  Not very sweet and a medium bitterness.  The beer is OK, but not my favorite IPA.
Good IPA, nice hop aroma, amber color with a good head.  Taste is sweet then bitter with hops all along the way. Over all this beer is up there for the IPAs.

This is awesome, one of my favorites now.  Aroma is super hoppy with floral and citrus tones.  It is a clear amber with a white colored head, leaving a nice lacing on the glass.  The taste is amazing, like biting into a hop.  Light sweet taste at first then goes very bitter, no bite even with the 9.4 ABV.  Medium bodied and smooth on the palate.  Overall one of the best IPAs I have had, defiantly going to drink this again.
roasty, grass, spruce, amber, medium sweetness, medium bitterness, lightly sour, medium body, creamy, average carbonation,
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Rotator IPA Series - ORyely IPA

review_blob: Aroma is more malty instead of hops.  It is darker for an IPA.  Taste is lightly sweet then bitter.  Smooth on the palate with a small head.  Not the best IPA, seems more like a pale ale.

Aroma is a nice floral with some spruce.  Poured a clear amber with a nice frothy head.  Taste was sweet then a nice bitter, hop character in the nose. Creamy on the palate with average carbonation and bitter finish.  Overall a great IPA.
cereal, floral, citrus, amber, medium bitterness, medium body, average carbonation,

With IPA on the label I expected a hoppy aroma, but was disappointed.  Color was a hazy amber with a minimal head. Medium bitterness taste, light body.  Overall not that great and shouldnt be called an IPA.
Light hoppy aroma, clear pour with small head. Taste sweet with slight bitter after taste. Overall not bad at their brewery with a live band.
beer_name: Prison Brews Go To Jail Ale

review_blob: Good hoppy aroma. Pours an orange color with a nice head. Taste is bitter sweet then to a strong bitter. Overall an awesome hoppy beer.

Aroma is sweet with malt not much hops, but I did just get over a cold. Appearance is amber with a small head. Taste is a good balance of bitter and malt, not much change on the palate. Overall nothing to write home about bit not horrible.

Not much aroma similar to any light American beer. Appearance is super clear yellow. Not much taste, just grains. Bitter on the palate, similar to a miller light. Overall the can labeling was better than the beer.
Hoppy citrus aroma not too strong. Appearance is clear orange tint. Sweet hop taste then very biter quickly on the palate. Overall not bad for a canned ipa.
UPDATED: JAN 25, 2012

Usually like IPA better, but this had a nice sweet aroma.  Appearance was clear golden.  Taste sweet at first then finished with a slight bitter on the palate.  Overall a great easy drinking pale ale.

Hop and malt smell with a good creamy head. Appearance was good for ipa. Taste was honey malt then turned into a nice strong bitter on the palate that lingered. Overall not bad, wished for more aroma hops and a sweeter body to balance to large amount of bittering hops.
Aroma isn?t too hoppy which was a little disappointing. Poured amber. Sweet hop taste that turned to a good bitter on the palate. Overall good beer but a little much at around $8.
beer_name: Rogue Nation Brutal India Pale Ale

review_blob: Can, first IPA I found in a can, $13 seemed alittle steep for a six pack, but it is a great IPA.  Good hop aroma and a sweet bitter after taste.
A great light beer, probably my favorite, just a little over priced.  Great beer for hot summer days or if your just wanting a light beer.  Good for float trips or hanging out around a lake.
sweet malt aroma, amber color with a thick creamy white head, has a good creamy malt taste, good beer

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Pours a gold with a small head, sweet skunky aroma, nutty brown taste, light on the palate

Not horrible for a cheap beer. It has a very clear pour with a white head that fades quickly. Taste has a hint of malts, no hop flavor, very watered down, but easy to drink if your not feeling a heavy beer.
Pours a dark amber color, aroma is strong malts with no hops smell, appearance has some floating hops in it, flavor is bitter malt, it is very bitter, not that impressed for an IPA.....
Pours a golden gold with a medium head. Strong aroma, it smells like grapefruit. Taste like strong hops with a touch of honey. This is a great beer, probably one of the best IPAs I have tried.
Tap. Pours a dark brown color with a decent sized head. Aroma is roasted malts and chocolate. Flavor is a bit on the weak side.
Bottle, deep golden amber, sweet malts, with a hint of caramel and toffee and a good balance of hops.  It has a nice medium head. Great fall beer.
